# .gitleaksignore — fingerprints gitleaks should skip on future scans.
#
# Rules:
#   1. Only add a fingerprint here after a human has confirmed the match is
#      either a placeholder / test value (Bucket A) or a credential that has
#      been revoked at the provider (Bucket C in .context/decisions/ADR-0011).
#   2. Never add a fingerprint for a real, still-live secret — rotate instead.
#   3. When adding, paste the `Fingerprint` value exactly as gitleaks printed
#      it. No surrounding quotes.
#
# Scope key:
#   BUCKET A — placeholder in docs / tests / env-template. Safe.
#   BUCKET C — real token shape that sat in git history; token revoked at
#              provider; now replaced with a placeholder in HEAD. See
#              .context/decisions/ADR-0011-gitleaks-scan-2026-04-21.md.

